*****
[1] Zambia (Central Province)
Date: Mon 16 Apr 2012
Source: Times of Zambia [edited]
http://allafrica.com/stories/201204161422.html


Typhoid cases in Kabwe have increased to 204 since the disease broke out 2 weeks ago. Kabwe Health District Management (KHDM) medical officer Abel Kabalo said in an interview that 2 more cases were recorded yesterday, 15 Apr 2012.

The department of water affairs has started mounting 11 water tanks in affected townships. Dr Kabalo said most of the patients had continued to receive treatment from their homes. He said yesterday, 15 Apr 2012, that only 2 cases were recorded, as compared to Saturday, 14 Apr 2012, when 11 new patients were treated in the Central Province capital.

